{{Infobox scientist |name = Axel Gavelin |image = Axel_Gavelin_1922.jpg |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1875|10|04}} |birth_place = [[Vilhelmina]] |death_date = {{death date and age|1947|06|14|1875|10|04|df=y}} |death_place = |residence = Sweden |citizenship = Sweden |nationality = Swedish |field = [[Geology]] |work_institutions = [[Geological Survey of Sweden]] |alma_mater = [[Uppsala University]] |doctoral_advisor = |children = [[Sven Gavelin]] |known_for = |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }}
'''Axel Olof Gavelin''' (1875–1947) was Swedish [[geologist]] active at the [[Geological Survey of Sweden]] of which he was director from 1916 to 1941. He studied both ice-dammed lakes and Precambrian rocks across Sweden.<ref>{{cite book |last= |first= |date=1948 |title=Kungl. fysiografiska sällskapets i Lund förhandlingar |trans-title=Proceedings of the Royal Physiographic Society at Lund |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Kungl_fysiografiska_sällskapets_i_Lund.html?id=VaMWAQAAIAAJ |language=Swedish |location=Lund, Sweden |publisher=[[Royal Physiographic Society in Lund]] |page=45 |isbn=}}</ref>
