[[Category:Nevada Test Site nuclear explosive tests|Sculpin]]

'''Phytosulfokines''' are  [[plant hormone]]s that belong to the growing class of plant [[peptide hormone]]s. Phytosulfokines are sulfated [[growth factor]]s strongly promoting proliferation of plant cells in cultures.

==References==
{{refbegin}}
*{{cite journal |vauthors=Matsubayashi Y, Sakagami Y |title=Phytosulfokine, sulfated peptides that induce the proliferation of single mesophyll cells of ''Asparagus officinalis L'' |journal=Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. |volume=93 |issue=15 |pages=7623–7 |date=July 1996 |pmid=8755525 |pmc=38796 |url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=8755525 |doi=10.1073/pnas.93.15.7623}}
{{refend}}

